conclusion: Understanding interaction between objects moving through air and landing on others
Objects are labeled A, B, C, D, E, and F in a 3D environment with arrows indicating movement
Object A is positioned on the left side of the image
Object B is positioned on the right side of the image
Both objects A and B move through the air and land on objects C, D, E, and F
Objects A and B come into contact with objects C, D, E, and F due to gravity
Objects A and B will collide with objects C, D, E, and F
